ass="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/pentagon-head-of-space-policy-appears-in-harrogate-court-after-boys-injured-in-collision" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/police-investigation-girl-death-surrey-international-search" target="_blank">Police launch international search for three people over death of girl in UK</a></h2><div class="description"> Detectives say people sought over suspected murder of 10-year-old girl in Surrey have probably left UK. Child’s body was found at a house in the village of Horsell, near Woking, Surrey. Detectives said they believed three people sought have left the UK.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:53:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/police-investigation-girl-death-surrey-international-search" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/owner-mortified-margate-gallery-was-closed-when-pedro-pascal-turned-up" target="_blank">Owner ‘mortified’ Margate gallery was closed when Pedro Pascal turned up</a></h2><div class="description"> Hollywood star had come to see exhibition featuring 17 images of his face. Jessica Rhodes Robb said she was 'mortified' the gallery was closed when the actor turned up for a visit. She was bemused to discover Pascal, 48, had turned up to the Rhodes Gallery in Margate.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:57:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/owner-mortified-margate-gallery-was-closed-when-pedro-pascal-turned-up" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/twinverclyde-17-sets-of-twins-to-start-school-in-one-scottish-authority" target="_blank">‘Twinverclyde’: 17 sets of twins to start school in one Scottish authority</a></h2><div class="description"> Inverclyde welcomes second largest number of twins on record to start primary education. School in area colloquially known as ‘Twinverclysde’ in Scottish local authority. School will welcome the twins for the first time on Friday 18 August.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:49:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/twinverclyde-17-sets-of-twins-to-start-school-in-one-scottish-authority" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/zelenskiy-sacks-all-military-recruitment-heads-over-frontline-bribes-scandal-ukraine" target="_blank">Zelenskiy sacks military recruitment heads over frontline bribes scandal</a></h2><div class="description"> Ukrainian president describes taking of cash from people who want to avoid conscription as form of treachery. Volodymyr Zelenskiy has announced the dismissal of all the heads of Ukraine’s regional military recruitment centres. Officials were accused of taking bribes from those seeking to avoid the frontlines.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 19:08:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/zelenskiy-sacks-all-military-recruitment-heads-over-frontline-bribes-scandal-ukraine" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/russians-fleeing-putin-war-find-a-home-in-phuket-thailand-ukraine" target="_blank">‘Main customers’: Russians fleeing Putin’s war find a home in Phuket</a></h2><div class="description"> Thai island has had influx of those either trying to avoid fighting in Ukraine or feel unwelcome in Europe. Aleksei* often sits alone on his balcony, and wonders if the past 18 months have been a strange dream. Last year, he was living with his mother and siblings in Moscow, and working in an IT job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 13:57:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/russians-fleeing-putin-war-find-a-home-in-phuket-thailand-ukraine" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/china-ukraine-peace-talks-saudi-arabia-russia" target="_blank">China has its own reasons for being at Ukraine peace talks in Saudi Arabia</a></h2><div class="description"> Gathering in Jeddah offers Beijing chance to placate global south and limit damage with west over Russia relations. China's envoy Li Hui arrived in Saudi Arabia, to join international talks on a peace deal for Ukraine this week, it was a pointed contrast with Beijing’s decision to skip a similar forum in Copenhagen in June.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:56:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/china-ukraine-peace-talks-saudi-arabia-russia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/russia-ukraine-war-at-a-glance-what-we-know-on-day-534-of-the-invasion" target="_blank">Russia-Ukraine war at a glance: what we know on day 534 of the invasion</a></h2><div class="description"> Air defence foils strike on Kyiv; Russia claims to have downed Ukrainian drone over Moscow. Mayor Vitali Klitschko posted to Telegram to state: “In addition to the debris of the rocket that fell on the territory of one of the capital's children’s hospitals, two more crash sites were found in the Obolon district of Kyiv.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 08:58:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/russia-ukraine-war-at-a-glance-what-we-know-on-day-534-of-the-invasion" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/11/supermodels-recreate-iconic-vogue-cover-30-years-on" target="_blank">Supermodels recreate iconic Vogue cover 30 years on</a></h2><div class="description"> Image will run across UK and US Vogue covers and coincides with upcoming documentary The Super Models. It is only missing Tatjana Patitz, who died earlier this year, from the 1990 edition of Vogue. Image will appear on UK and U.S. editions with the cover line: "The Greatest of All Time"</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 18:32:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/11/supermodels-recreate-iconic-vogue-cover-30-years-on" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/world-scout-jamborees-chaos-south-korea-rains-heat-illness" target="_blank">‘The scouts were getting sicker and sicker’: inside the chaos of the world jamboree</a></h2><div class="description"> A Swedish scout leader diarises a challenging 10 days in South Korea. Moa Mannerström, 23, was trying to keep up her scouts’ spirits. The 25th World Scout Jamboree descended into chaos amid scorching heat, heavy downpours and poor organisation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:18:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/world-scout-jamborees-chaos-south-korea-rains-heat-illness" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/oscar-at-the-crown-review-assembly-george-square-gardens-edinburgh" target="_blank">Oscar at the Crown review – going Wilde in the nightclub</a></h2><div class="description"> Oscar Wilde hides in a bunker on a dystopian dance floor, but while there is much high-energy music there is little drama. The immersive production is set on a circular stage and tells Wilde's story from a series of mobile podiums. The show is held at Assembly George Square Gardens, Edinburgh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 20:00:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/oscar-at-the-crown-review-assembly-george-square-gardens-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/11/key-longer-life-why-walk-exactly-3967-steps-day" target="_blank">The key to a longer life? Why I tried to walk exactly 3,967 steps in a day</a></h2><div class="description"> A study says this is the number needed to cut risk of dying from any cause - so I took on the task. Researchers found as few as 2,337 steps a day started to lessen the risk of cardiovascular diseases. As many steps as 3,967 a day is the exact number at which a person should take the most steps to reduce risk of death.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/11/key-longer-life-why-walk-exactly-3967-steps-day" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/12/how-does-it-feel-to-live-without-a-smartphone-almost-spiritual" target="_blank">How does it feel to live without a smartphone? ‘Almost spiritual’</a></h2><div class="description"> Angelo Profera's smartphone gave up the ghost earlier this year. He'd started feeling like the phone was more a chore than convenience. He left the shop with a phone that had no internet and could only receive calls and text messages. It was a bold move for a smartphone native, and he was initially worried his new device might cause problems.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:00:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/12/how-does-it-feel-to-live-without-a-smartphone-almost-spiritual" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/11/i-refuse-to-get-old-how-readers-strive-to-keep-dementia-at-bay" target="_blank">‘I refuse to get old’: how readers strive to keep dementia at bay</a></h2><div class="description"> Researchers say lifestyle changes could prevent up to 40% of dementia cases. Our readers share their efforts to mitigate the risk. Sarah Chester’s mother first started showing symptoms of dementia 15 years ago, and she found herself thinking: “If I don’t really get my act together now, will I have the same trajectory?”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:07:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/11/i-refuse-to-get-old-how-readers-strive-to-keep-dementia-at-bay" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/11/inside-the-world-of-tvs-disabled-dating-shows-netflix-down-for-love-undateables" target="_blank">‘I don’t like people feeling sorry for us’: inside the world of TV’s disabled dating shows</a></h2><div class="description"> New Netflix series Down for Love follows people who have learning disabilities as they embark on a journey to find partners. The show follows on from the success of New Zealand’s Down For Love, which was developed in New Zealand by disability-first production company Attitude Pictures.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 12:00:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/11/inside-the-world-of-tvs-disabled-dating-shows-netflix-down-for-love-undateables" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/my-wife-finds-her-mothers-rightwing-rants-hurtful-should-we-cut-her-off" target="_blank">My wife finds her mother’s rightwing rants hurtful. Should we cut her off? | Ask Annalisa Barbieri</a></h2><div class="description"> My mother-in-law is a solitary person with no friends, although she has been married to my wife’s dad for many years. She spends entire days alone looking at rightwing websites while he is at work. The opinions she hears exacerbate her racist, homophobic views. Put your relationship first and maintain a united front.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 13:30:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/my-wife-finds-her-mothers-rightwing-rants-hurtful-should-we-cut-her-off" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/11/back-three-may-be-best-way-for-rejigged-england-to-counter-colombias-fire" target="_blank">Back three may be best way for rejigged England to counter Colombia’s fire  | Jonas Eidevall</a></h2><div class="description"> England go into Women’s World Cup quarter-final without Lauren James. Sarina Wiegman has to make biggest fix yet as England face Colombia. Sweden, Japan, Spain and the Netherlands are the four teams with greatest clarity in the draw. Australia prepared for the tournament with Sam Kerr as their No 9 but lost her until the closing moments of their last-16 match.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 19:00:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/11/back-three-may-be-best-way-for-rejigged-england-to-counter-colombias-fire" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/12/womens-world-cup-2023-matildas-vs-france-match-preview" target="_blank">Defining World Cup moment on the line as Matildas look to make history | Kieran Pender</a></h2><div class="description"> The Matildas face a do-or-die moment for the third time in a row. Australia face their toughest match yet against France’s lethal attack. The hopes and dreams of Australia on the shoulders of 23 women on Saturday afternoon. Les Bleues may fear the same of Tony Gustavsson's side.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:00:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/12/womens-world-cup-2023-matildas-vs-france-match-preview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/colombia-world-cup-journey-england-quarter-final" target="_blank">Powerful and defiant: how Colombia’s World Cup journey gripped a nation</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia players protested against lack of resources at home. Players have become national heroes before quarter-final against England. Women's team will play England in last 16 of the World Cup on Friday night. Colombia will be hoping to qualify for last eight of the tournament in Brazil.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 14:54:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/colombia-world-cup-journey-england-quarter-final" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/spain-secure-spot-in-world-cup-semi-finals-with-extra-time-win-over-netherlands" target="_blank">Spain secure spot in World Cup semi-finals with extra-time win over Netherlands</a></h2><div class="description"> Spain will play a World Cup semi-final for the first time, against Sweden in Auckland next Tuesday. The 19-year-old Barcelona winger salvaged a lot more than Spain’s tournament. She redeemed their idea of who they are, the idea that this great generation can still be great.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 04:03:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/spain-secure-spot-in-world-cup-semi-finals-with-extra-time-win-over-netherlands" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/burnley-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report" target="_blank">Erling Haaland launches Manchester City to opening victory at Burnley</a></h2><div class="description"> Manchester City beat Burnley 1-0 in their Premier League opener at Turf Moor. The game was billed as a box-office Premier League curtain raiser and did not disappoint. Manchester City have won the Premier League three times in a row. Burnley were promoted as Championship winners after being promoted to the top flight.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 21:08:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/burnley-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/tottenham-will-move-on-quickly-from-harry-kane-exit-says-postecoglou" target="_blank">Tottenham will move on quickly from Harry Kane exit, says Postecoglou</a></h2><div class="description"> Harry Kane flies to Germany to complete £100m Bayern Munich move. Kane flew to Germany on Friday evening and was expected to undergo his medical. Tottenham accepted a bid that could be worth almost £100million. Tottenham chairman Daniel Levy renegotiated elements of the fee at a late stage.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 21:30:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/tottenham-will-move-on-quickly-from-harry-kane-exit-says-postecoglou" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/borthwick-puts-faith-in-saracens-spine-as-england-aim-for-redemption-rugby-union" target="_blank">Borthwick puts faith in Saracens spine as England aim for redemption</a></h2><div class="description"> England coach Steve Borthwick knows the impact a Saracens core can have. Elliot Daly's international form nosedived in the final years of Eddie Jones’s tenure. England coach can ill-afford to lose to Wales in next World Cup warm-up.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:21:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/borthwick-puts-faith-in-saracens-spine-as-england-aim-for-redemption-rugby-union" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/roberto-firmino-hits-hat-trick-to-kickstart-saudi-pro-league-in-style" target="_blank">Skills, spills and a dash of controversy: the Saudi Pro League kicks off</a></h2><div class="description"> Roberto Firmino bagged a hat-trick in the first match of the Saudi Pro League. Al-Ahli beat Al-Hazm 1-0 in Jeddah on Friday night. The game was the first of the new season in the world's second most disruptive sporting competition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 21:22:17 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/roberto-firmino-hits-hat-trick-to-kickstart-saudi-pro-league-in-style" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/josh-tarling-and-ben-wiggins-claim-world-championship-medals-for-britain-cycling" target="_blank">Josh Tarling and Ben Wiggins claim world championship medals for Britain</a></h2><div class="description"> Remco Evenepoel becomes first Belgian rider to win elite men’s world title. Josh Tarling gets bronze in elite individual individual time trial. Ben Wiggins takes silver behind Oscar Chamberlain in junior event. Tarling and Wiggins claim medals in men's time trial disciplines at world championships.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:25:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/josh-tarling-and-ben-wiggins-claim-world-championship-medals-for-britain-cycling" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/ewing-womens-open-golf" target="_blank">Ewing takes inspiration from Harman to open up big lead at Women’s Open</a></h2><div class="description"> American earns five-shot lead after 36 holes at Walton Heath. Ally Ewing admits she had been inspired by Brian Harman’s Open triumph. The 30-year-old from Mississippi also picked up further shots on the 11th and 16th before dropping her only shot of the day on the last.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 21:53:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/ewing-womens-open-golf" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/liverpool-chelsea-moises-caicedo-brighton" target="_blank">Chelsea ready to raise Moisés Caicedo offer after Liverpool agree £110m deal</a></h2><div class="description"> Chelsea offered £100m for top target and will not give up on Moisés Caicedo. Club also make bid of £55m for Southampton's Roméo Lavia. Liverpool had a £110m offer for the Ecuadorian accepted by Brighton on Thursday night.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 19:55:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/liverpool-chelsea-moises-caicedo-brighton" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/hull-kr-and-leigh-await-chance-to-end-long-search-for-challenge-cup-glory-rugby-league" target="_blank">Challenge Cup final: Hull KR and Leigh look to end long wait for glory</a></h2><div class="description"> Hull FC and Hull Kingston Rovers share similar histories where a win will provide a lift and a legacy for their working-class communities. The first Challenge Cup final since 1986 which doesn't feature any of Leeds, St Helens, Wigan or Warrington emphasises the rarity of what is in store.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 13:04:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/11/hull-kr-and-leigh-await-chance-to-end-long-search-for-challenge-cup-glory-rugby-league" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/crooked-house-burnt-out-pub-historic-landmark" target="_blank">Why this lament for a burnt-out pub? Is it because Britain seems a bit of a Crooked House these days? | Marina Hyde</a></h2><div class="description"> Adam and Carly Taylor took ownership of the Crooked House just over a fortnight ago. But it was gutted by fire nine days later, sparking national outrage. Within 48 hours of the blaze, the structural remains of the pub were hastily reduced to rubble by a digger – without council permission.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:18:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/crooked-house-burnt-out-pub-historic-landmark" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/11/ella-baron-on-rishi-sunak-and-the-climate-crisis-cartoon" target="_blank">Ella Baron on Rishi Sunak and the climate crisis – cartoon</a></h2><div class="description"> CNN.com will feature iReporter photos in a weekly Travel Snapshots gallery. Please submit your best shots for next week's gallery of snapshots of the world's most beautiful beaches. Submit your best photos of the best beaches in the world to visit CNN iReport.com/Travel.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 18:30:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/11/ella-baron-on-rishi-sunak-and-the-climate-crisis-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/ecuador-presidential-candidate-killing-violence-drugs" target="_blank">In Ecuador, a presidential candidate was assassinated. The tragedy is that no one was surprised | Jorge Núñez</a></h2><div class="description"> Our country is locked in a spiral of killing and violence, says Jorge Núñez. During Guillermo Lasso’s presidency, eight public officials or candidates for office have been killed and several have survived murder attempts. How did Ecuador go from being one of the safest countries in Latin America to being one the most violent countries in the region?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 14:00:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/ecuador-presidential-candidate-killing-violence-drugs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/gen-z-entitled-young-people-inflation-pay-rises" target="_blank">Tinned tomatoes for dinner, can barely pay the rent: pity Gen Zs as they’re blamed for inflation | Daisy Jones</a></h2><div class="description"> Young people are asking for pay rises, but it’s not ‘entitled’ to want more from life than endless emails and cheap pasta until you die. Young people today are being more assertive in the workplace – not out of entitlement, but pure necessity.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 12:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/gen-z-entitled-young-people-inflation-pay-rises" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/greta-thunberg-greenwashing-edinburgh-book-festival-arts" target="_blank">Of course Greta Thunberg is right to call out greenwashing, but the reality can be messy | Charlotte Higgins</a></h2><div class="description"> Environmental campaigner Greta Thunberg withdraws from Edinburgh book festival. She was due to speak at the festival's main sponsor Baillie Gifford, who invests in fossil fuel companies. She said the fossil fuel industry's sponsorship of cultural events allowed them to keep the social licence to continue operating.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 13:10:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/greta-thunberg-greenwashing-edinburgh-book-festival-arts" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/britain-deer-population-ecological-disaster-wolves-humans-predators" target="_blank">Britain’s surging deer population is causing an ecological disaster. I have a solution: wolves | George Monbiot</a></h2><div class="description"> Humans have failed to keep numbers down. Wolves and lynx would better be described as mesopredators. The wolf that didn’t howl helps solve the mystery of how this country is still alive, says Simon Tisdall. We talk here of wolves as “top” predators, but our native top predators were lions, hyenas, bears and scimitar cats.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 11:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/britain-deer-population-ecological-disaster-wolves-humans-predators" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/11/china-economic-problems-show-things-are-seriously-amiss" target="_blank">China’s economic problems show things are seriously amiss | George Magnus</a></h2><div class="description"> China’s leaders referred to the economic recovery this year as ‘torturous’ Underlying longer-term weaknesses in the economy are bound up with Beijing's repressive political system. Consumer prices in July were lower than a year ago, suggesting it might be on the cusp of deflation. And foreign trade in July showed a sharp fall in exports due to weak global demand.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 14:17:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/11/china-economic-problems-show-things-are-seriously-amiss" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/11/50th-birthday-hip-hop-voice-truth-new-york-world-protest" target="_blank">Hip-hop gave us Public Enemy, Lauryn Hill, Kendrick Lamar: after 50 years, this music demands proper respect | Nels Abbey</a></h2><div class="description"> Clive Campbell (popularly known as Kool Herc), an 18-year-old DJ, hosted a party at 1520 Sedgwick Avenue in the Bronx. Unbeknownst to the men and women dancing the night away, they were witnessing the birth of a socioeconomic and political miracle. Hip-hop is now an instrument for learning and a weapon for protest.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 09:00:32 GMT</s