</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/11/saudi-arabia-asks-to-join-uk-italy-japan-joint-air-combat-programme-tempest-gcap" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/fox-corp-chief-legal-officer-exits" target="_blank">Fox Corp marks another high-level exit with legal chief Viet Dinh stepping down</a></h2><div class="description"> Viet Dinh’s exit another major departure from the network since its $787.5m settlement with Dominion Voting Systems in April. Dinh joined Fox in 2018 and headed its legal and compliance divisions during the months-long legal battle sparked by the network's coverage of false claims that Dominion rigged the election.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 22:07:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/fox-corp-chief-legal-officer-exits" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/niger-captive-leader-losing-weight-in-inhumane-conditions-daughter-reveals-mohamed-bazoum" target="_blank">Niger’s captive leader losing weight in inhumane conditions, daughter says</a></h2><div class="description"> Zazia Bazoum says she is in near daily phone contact with her father, mother and brother. She says they are living without clean water and relying on supplies of rice and pasta. The president's daughter was on holiday in France when he was detained by his own guard last month.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 11:48:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/niger-captive-leader-losing-weight-in-inhumane-conditions-daughter-reveals-mohamed-bazoum" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/more-than-2000-people-missing-at-sea-as-use-of-deadliest-route-to-eu-doubles" target="_blank">More than 2,000 people missing at sea as use of deadliest route to EU doubles</a></h2><div class="description"> Europe’s border and coast guard agency said on Friday irregular arrivals had risen by 13% between January and July to 176,100, the highest number for the period since 2016. Hundreds die as route from Libya or Tunisia to Greece or Italy made in unseaworthy, overloaded boats.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:59:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/11/more-than-2000-people-missing-at-sea-as-use-of-deadliest-route-to-eu-doubles" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/11/elon-musk-mark-zuckerberg-cage-fight-italy-government" target="_blank">Musk says proposed Zuckerberg cage fight to be held at ‘epic location’ in Italy</a></h2><div class="description"> X owner in talks with government over historic site for event – though Colosseum and Rome ruled out. The owner of X Corp and the chief executive of Facebook-owner Meta first raised the idea of a one-on-one scrap in June. The challenge came as Zuckerberg prepared to launch Threads, a rival microblogging site to Musk’s now rebranded Twitter platform.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:40:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/11/elon-musk-mark-zuckerberg-cage-fight-italy-government" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/11/scientists-fifth-force-nature" target="_blank">Scientists may be on brink of discovering fifth force of nature</a></h2><div class="description"> Experts closing in on potentially identifying new force after surprise wobble of subatomic particle. According to current understanding, there are four fundamental forces in nature, three of which are explained by the standard model of particle physics. The theory that a fifth force of nature could exist has been given a boost thanks to unexpected wobbling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 12:01:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/11/scientists-fifth-force-nature" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/frankie-thompson-liv-ello-body-show-review-pleasance-courtyard-edinburgh" target="_blank">Frankie Thompson and Liv Ello: Body Show review – a total takedown of gendered expectations</a></h2><div class="description"> Frankie Thompson and Liv Ello craft a rich exploration of eating disorders and gender dysphoria. The pair combine to bring their distinctive take on theatre to new heights. The heteronormative pastiche sets the tone for a show about gendered expectations placed upon bodies, forcing their owners into uncomfortable spaces.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 17:57:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/frankie-thompson-liv-ello-body-show-review-pleasance-courtyard-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/11/i-didnt-have-a-second-thought-why-jennifer-lawrence-and-scarlett-johansson-are-stripping-off-on-screen" target="_blank">‘I didn’t have a second thought’: why Jennifer Lawrence and Scarlett Johansson are stripping off on screen</a></h2><div class="description"> In films like No Hard Feelings, Joy Ride and Asteroid City, full-frontal female nudity is back. Full frontal nudity is making a comeback on screen in a crop of summer comedies. In Adele Lim’s new Asian-led comedy Joy Ride, which channels the raucous spirit of Bridesmaids, has been keen to point out that a body double was used.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 07:00:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/11/i-didnt-have-a-second-thought-why-jennifer-lawrence-and-scarlett-johansson-are-stripping-off-on-screen" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/11/16th-century-texts-worth-25m-dollars-up-for-auction-t-kimball-brooker-sothebys" target="_blank">‘Unparalleled treasure trove’ of 16th-century texts worth $25m up for auction</a></h2><div class="description"> T Kimball Brooker amassed more than 1,300 titles over the course of six decades. Early manuscript of Leonardo da Vinci’s treatise on painting is expected to fetch $25m at auction. Collection features French and Italian volumes in their original bindings.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 14:05:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/11/16th-century-texts-worth-25m-dollars-up-for-auction-t-kimball-brooker-sothebys" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/11/authors-boycott-edinburgh-book-festival-sponsors-fossil-fuel-links" target="_blank">Authors threaten boycott of Edinburgh book festival over sponsors’ fossil fuel links</a></h2><div class="description"> An open letter signed by more than 50 authors calls for Baillie Gifford to be dropped as main sponsor for 2024. Authors include Zadie Smith, Ali Smith and Katherine Rundell. Company has up to £5bn invested in corporations that profit from fossil fuels.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 12:45:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/11/authors-boycott-edinburgh-book-festival-sponsors-fossil-fuel-links" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/11/red-white-and-royal-blue-review-amazon-gay-romance" target="_blank">Red, White and Royal Blue review – bland gay romance opts for beige</a></h2><div class="description"> Amazon’s adaptation of the hit romance novel Red, White and Royal Blue is listless. The film aims to show that gay love stories can be just as basic and sickly sweet as straight ones. It's a win that it exists perhaps, but a loss for those hoping for something better than a Hallmark movie.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 16:58:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/11/red-white-and-royal-blue-review-amazon-gay-romance" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/playwright-sam-holcroft-a-mirror-interview" target="_blank">Playwright Sam Holcroft: ‘It felt like everyone else got a rulebook that I didn’t’</a></h2><div class="description"> Sam Holcroft’s latest play, A Mirror, mixes her keen eye for human behaviour and her experiences in North Korea. The play is about making theatre in a country where art is state censored. Director Jeremy Herrin describes it as a ‘Russian doll series of plays within plays’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 13:00:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/11/playwright-sam-holcroft-a-mirror-interview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/the-toughest-qualification-in-finance-why-its-now-more-achievable-than-ever" target="_blank">The toughest qualification in finance? Why it’s now more achievable than ever</a></h2><div class="description"> The CFA charter is considered the gold standard for those seeking to work in finance. But it has long been regarded as notoriously challenging – now, it’s become more accessible and appealing to a broader range of applicants. 60 years since candidates sat the first exams, the CFA Program has changed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:41:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/the-toughest-qualification-in-finance-why-its-now-more-achievable-than-ever" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/fighting-fires-with-finance-how-investment-professionals-can-help-tackle-the-climate-emergency" target="_blank">Fighting fires with finance: how investment professionals can help tackle the climate emergency</a></h2><div class="description"> As the climate crisis becomes impossible to ignore, the world of finance is waking up to the risks it poses. These include the devastating effects of a warming planet, the regulatory impact of the global transition to a low-carbon economy, and the reputational risk of being a laggard in the eyes of eco-conscious consumers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:31:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/fighting-fires-with-finance-how-investment-professionals-can-help-tackle-the-climate-emergency" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/from-crypto-sleuth-to-carbon-cutter-five-little-known-jobs-you-can-do-as-a-chartered-financial-analyst" target="_blank">From crypto sleuth to carbon cutter: five little-known jobs you can do as a chartered financial analyst</a></h2><div class="description"> Chartered financial analysts typically go into the financial sector at an investment firm. But there are a number of less familiar career paths that can be taken too. About half of the world’s portfolio managers are CFA charterholders, according to CFA Institute. Here are five lesser-known career paths you can take too.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:40:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/from-crypto-sleuth-to-carbon-cutter-five-little-known-jobs-you-can-do-as-a-chartered-financial-analyst" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/invest-in-your-future-why-a-career-in-finance-can-make-a-positive-impact-on-the-world" target="_blank">Invest in your future: why a career in finance can make a positive impact on the world</a></h2><div class="description"> The finance sector has long been thought of as problematic when it comes to the impact it has on society. But things are changing – financiers are increasingly starting to tackle pressing problems such as the climate crisis and inequality. The global transition to clean energy and a low carbon economy requires a massive reallocation of resources, while the widespread embrace of so-called ESG factors has proved to be a genuine paradi.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:31:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/invest-in-your-future-why-a-career-in-finance-can-make-a-positive-impact-on-the-world" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/11/from-normandy-to-the-dordogne-readers-favourite-spots-in-france" target="_blank">From Normandy to the Dordogne: readers’ favourite spots in France</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendaye is a less-discovered corner of the Bay of Biscay bordering Spain. Sleeper trains between Paris and Hendaye mean sustainable travel is possible. Head to Le Palmier for great pizza and a lovely little artisan market. If you’re more adventurous, Hendaye’s sheltered bay offers the perfect playground for beginner surfers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 10:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/11/from-normandy-to-the-dordogne-readers-favourite-spots-in-france" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/11/cocktail-of-the-week-maria-bradford-leone-star-recipe" target="_blank">Cocktail of the week: Maria Bradford’s Leone star – recipe | The good mixer</a></h2><div class="description"> A west African twist on the prosecco cocktail, featuring pineapple and star fruit as striking additions, is named after Sierra Leone’s national football team. You’ll need a juicer to make it, and you'll need to use it to make the drink.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 15:00:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/11/cocktail-of-the-week-maria-bradford-leone-star-recipe" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/have-sex-in-the-morning-bake-at-night-experts-reveal-the-perfect-time-of-day-for-everything" target="_blank">Have sex in the morning – but always bake at night: experts reveal the perfect time of day for everything</a></h2><div class="description"> Picking the optimum time to do things can make a real difference in life. Here’s how to make the most of your 24 hours: How do you spend your time in the perfect place to spend the rest of your life? Find out more about how to spend your day in the UK.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 10:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/11/have-sex-in-the-morning-bake-at-night-experts-reveal-the-perfect-time-of-day-for-everything" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/11/raspberry-limoncello-white-chocolate-swiss-roll-recipe-benjamina-ebuehi" target="_blank">Benjamina Ebuehi’s recipe for raspberry, limoncello and white chocolate swiss roll | The new vegan</a></h2><div class="description"> A classic British classic, with endless variations, is easier to make than you might think. Adding a bit of oil to the sponge provides extra security against cracks when rolling. Fresh cream and limoncello make an appearance when you want to make a more impressive swiss roll.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 14:00:50 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/11/raspberry-limoncello-white-chocolate-swiss-roll-recipe-benjamina-ebuehi" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/10/fashion-statement-tekla-towels" target="_blank">Throw the towel in: why fashion’s new accessory is in your bathroom</a></h2><div class="description"> Kristoffer Juhl, co-founder of Danish homeware brand Tekla, knows all about this. Growing up, he says ‘you just bought the towels your mother told you to buy’ for most of your adult life. ‘There was simply nowhere that specialised in nice towels that you’d want people to see'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 11:30:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/10/fashion-statement-tekla-towels" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/11/and-just-like-that-20-memorable-looks-and-what-they-tell-us-about-fashion-today" target="_blank">And Just Like That … 20 memorable looks – and what they tell us about fashion today</a></h2><div class="description"> The resin replica of a pigeon made by Irish designer JW Anderson is available for £650. It is a visual gag that speaks to fashion’s love of a meme. It's also a not-so-humblebrag, in that you must be able to afford a car or not be on your way to an actual job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 09:36:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/11/and-just-like-that-20-memorable-looks-and-what-they-tell-us-about-fashion-today" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Niger coup: why do so many want France out and Russia in? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> On 26 July, a group of soldiers removed Niger's democratically elected president from power citing security concerns and economic mismanagement. Crowds waved Russian flags and chanted slogans against France, the country's former coloniser. The anti-French – and more widely anti-foreign – sentiment has rapidly become a key element of how the coup is being framed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:37:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Extreme weather: glacial flooding, wildfires and hailstorms cause havoc across the world  – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Countries across the globe are facing a range of extreme weather events. Severe flooding has affected parts of Europe including Sweden and Slovenia. Human-caused climate change is supercharging extreme weather across the world, driving more frequent and more deadly disasters, from heatwaves to floods to wildfires.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:36:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/luton-fans-share-your-mood-before-the-clubs-first-premier-league-game" target="_blank">Luton fans: share your mood before the club’s first Premier League game</a></h2><div class="description"> Luton Town return to the Premier League for the first time in 31 years. The Hatters face Brighton at the top of the table on Saturday afternoon. Luton fans want to know how excited they are about their chances. Do you have any memories of the last time you were in the top flight?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 11:28:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/luton-fans-share-your-mood-before-the-clubs-first-premier-league-game" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-employees-how-will-you-be-affected-by-the-retailer-entering-administration" target="_blank">Wilko employees: how will you be affected by the retailer entering administration?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 12,000 jobs at risk after struggling to agree a rescue deal. The family-owned household and garden products retailer is expected to close dozens of outlets. We want to hear from workers at Wilko following the news that dozens of stores are expected to shut.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:04:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-employees-how-will-you-be-affected-by-the-retailer-entering-administration" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">People in Maui: how have you been affected by the wildfires?</a></h2><div class="description"> At least 53 people have died in wildfires on the Hawaiian island of Maui. The fires, fanned by strong winds from Hurricane Dora, destroyed businesses in the historic town of Lahaina. There have been 13 evacuations for three fires and at least two dozen people injured.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 09:15:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/uk-mortgage-holders-share-your-experience-of-rising-costs" target="_blank">UK mortgage holders: share your experience of repossession</a></h2><div class="description"> There have been 13 consecutive increases in mortgage interest rates placing further strain on homeowners already struggling with soaring bills. We would like to hear from people who are struggling with their mortgage payments and are facing repossession. The ongoing cost of living crisis has placed a growing burden on UK households.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 08:36:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/uk-mortgage-holders-share-your-experience-of-rising-costs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/how-search-for-ufos-reached-us-congress-podcast" target="_blank">How the search for UFOs reached the US Congress – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The quest to discover whether or not we're alone in the universe has become an obsession for many Americans. Now it has gone beyond internet forums, YouTube channels and kooky podcasts. Pentagon has said pilots are seeing things up in the sky that they can’t explain. A few weeks ago, spaceships got their day in Congress.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 02:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/how-search-for-ufos-reached-us-congress-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/11/power-junk-food-companies-washington-podcast" target="_blank">The power of junk food companies in Washington – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Jonathan Freedland speaks to Dr Eduardo J Gómez of Lehigh University, on how his new book Junk Food Politics taught him about the power of lobbyists. He also discusses the growing rate of obesity in the US, why are politicians not stepping in to improve nutrition?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 04:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/11/power-junk-food-companies-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/best-of-2023-so-far-i-know-where-the-bodies-are-buried-one-womans-mission-to-change-how-the-police-investigate-podcast" target="_blank">Best of 2023… so far: ‘I know where the bodies are buried’: one woman’s mission to change how the police investigate rape – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Every Friday in August we will publish some of our favourite audio long reads of 2023. This week, Betsy Stanko leads an investigation into why the police have been failing so badly to tackle sexual violence. But is there any chance of fixing a system that seems so broken?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 04:00:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/best-of-2023-so-far-i-know-where-the-bodies-are-buried-one-womans-mission-to-change-how-the-police-investigate-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/10/premier-league-season-preview-liverpool-to-wolves-football-weekly" target="_blank">Premier League season preview: Liverpool to Wolves – Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Max Rushden is joined by Barry Glendenning, Jonathan Wilson and Mark Langdon for our second Premier League preview show. The panel ponder whether Liverpool can plug a hole in their midfield and get themselves back among the top four. They also discuss how Manchester United and Newcastle will fare with the added rigour of Champions League football to contend with.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:48:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/10/premier-league-season-preview-liverpool-to-wolves-football-weekly" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: are we any closer to understanding long Covid? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Ian Sample hears from Scotland’s Astronomer Royal, Prof Catherine Heymans, about her experience of long Covid and how it has affected her life. He also speaks to Prof Danny Altmann, an immunologist at Imperial College London, about the scientific understanding of the condition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 04:00:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/10/summer-picks-are-we-any-closer-to-understanding-long-covid-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">The Qur’an burnings in Sweden: who is fanning the flames? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The act of burning a holy book in Sweden is not of itself illegal. But a spate of burnings has resulted in outrage at home and abroad – and potentially far-reaching consequences. Sweden is facing diplomatic pressure from the Organisation of Islamic Cooperation, which represents 57 countries. At the same time it is fretting over the support of Turkey to allow it to become a full Nato member.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 02:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/audio/2023/aug/10/the-quran-burnings-in-sweden-who-is-fanning-the-flames-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/between-two-worlds-life-of-png-tribe-leader-and-plantation-owner-honoured" target="_blank">Between two worlds: life of PNG tribe leader and plantation owner honoured</a></h2><div class="description"> Joe Leahy, owner of the famed Kilima coffee plantation, remembered in week-long traditional ceremony in Papua New Guinea. Kilima was purchased from the Ganiga in the early 1970s by a then young Johannes ‘Joe’ Leahy. He spent years building up and then decades mourning its destruction. Earlier this month Leahy died, aged 85, inside the house he lived in most of his life.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 20:00:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/between-two-worlds-life-of-png-tribe-leader-and-plantation-owner-honoured" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/biden-climate-bill-inflation-reduction-act" target="_blank">Green investment boom and electric car sales: six key things about Biden’s climate bill</a></h2><div class="description"> The $369bn Inflation Reduction Act has boosted clean energy and EV cars. Joe Biden hailed the bill as ‘one of the most significant laws in 